83
00:06:54.516 --> 00:06:58.509
<b>waited for the coffin
and remembered.</b>


84
00:06:58.554 --> 00:07:01.489
<b>They wonder if their sons
are still alive...</b>


85
00:07:01.523 --> 00:07:03.218
<b>and why the world sits back...</b>

86
00:07:03.258 --> 00:07:04.816
<b>and allows
the Vietnamese government...</b>


87
00:07:04.860 --> 00:07:08.626
<b>to flagrantly violate
the Geneva Convention.</b>


88
00:07:08.664 --> 00:07:11.098
<b>Rumors of physical
and mental torture...</b>


89
00:07:11.133 --> 00:07:13.567
<b>have made
the wait more agonizing.</b>


90
00:07:13.602 --> 00:07:17.766
<b>The families were reassured
by a deeply moved president.</b>


91
00:07:17.806 --> 00:07:21.003
<b>We write no last chapters...</b>

92
00:07:21.043 --> 00:07:23.204
<b>we close no books...</b>

93
00:07:23.245 --> 00:07:25.713
<b>we put away no final memories.</b>

94
00:07:25.747 --> 00:07:28.409
<b>An end to America's
involvement in Vietnam...</b>


95
00:07:28.450 --> 00:07:30.918
<b>cannot come
before we have achieved...</b>


96
00:07:30.953 --> 00:07:35.287
<b>the fullest possible accounting
of those missing in action.</b>


97
00:08:04.920 --> 00:08:05.909
<b>Colonel Yin...</b>

98
00:08:07.422 --> 00:08:11.051
<b>you may not give a damn
about the Geneva Convention...</b>


99
00:08:11.093 --> 00:08:14.722
<b>but someday you're gonna
be held accountable.</b>


100
00:08:14.763 --> 00:08:19.700
<b>The Geneva Convention applies
to prisoners of war.</b>


101
00:08:19.735 --> 00:08:23.171
<b>You men are not
prisoners of war.</b>


102
00:08:23.205 --> 00:08:25.503
<b>You are common criminals.</b>

103
00:08:25.540 --> 00:08:27.132
<b>I have repeatedly told you...</b>

104
00:08:27.175 --> 00:08:29.803
<b>that there is no escape
from my camp...</b>


105
00:08:29.845 --> 00:08:34.509
<b>unless you consider
death an escape.</b>


106
00:08:34.549 --> 00:08:36.881
<b>You are surrounded by cliffs...</b>

107
00:08:36.918 --> 00:08:39.785
<b>mountains,
jungles full of man traps...</b>


108
00:08:39.821 --> 00:08:43.313
<b>and a bridge that is impassable.</b>

109
00:08:43.358 --> 00:08:48.455
<b>None of you have ever escaped,
and none of you will.</b>


110
00:08:48.497 --> 00:08:52.456
<b>The only way for you to leave
my camp...</b>


111
00:08:52.501 --> 00:08:56.130
<b>is if Braddock confesses.</b>

112
00:08:57.839 --> 00:09:01.900
<b>He defends the country
that has forgotten you...</b>


113
00:09:01.943 --> 00:09:07.142
<b>an outlaw nation
the rest of the world reviles!</b>


114
00:09:12.988 --> 00:09:18.051
<b>They are killing
your ambassadors of the evil...</b>


115
00:09:18.093 --> 00:09:19.856
<b>in every part of the world.</b>

116
00:09:41.183 --> 00:09:42.377
<b>I have something for you.</b>

117
00:09:48.090 --> 00:09:50.320
<b>Hey, it's a beaut.</b>

118
00:09:50.359 --> 00:09:51.621
<b>It's a good two inches.</b>

119
00:09:51.660 --> 00:09:53.218
<b>Angelo says thanks.</b>

120
00:10:00.402 --> 00:10:02.563
<b>What he give you?</b>

121
00:10:02.604 --> 00:10:04.697
<b>A B-52.</b>

122
00:10:04.740 --> 00:10:06.503
<b>It's just a worm
for his chicken.</b>


123
00:10:15.784 --> 00:10:18.082
<b>You know, I got to learn
to keep my mouth shut.</b>


124
00:10:18.120 --> 00:10:20.179
<b>What do you do?
You never shoot your mouth off.</b>


125
00:10:20.222 --> 00:10:22.122
<b>I try to decide
if what I'm going to say...</b>


126
00:10:22.157 --> 00:10:23.317
<b>is worth getting hit for.</b>

127
00:10:25.861 --> 00:10:27.021
<b>Wish I could do that.</b>

128
00:10:27.062 --> 00:10:28.188
<b>Franklin?</b>

129
00:10:28.230 --> 00:10:29.527
<b>Hey, it's hot. 
I'm sweating.</b>

130
00:10:31.533 --> 00:10:32.864
<b>Looks like the malaria again.</b>

131
00:10:32.901 --> 00:10:33.890
<b>Hey...</b>

132
00:10:42.411 --> 00:10:44.504
<b>What the hell is Harry doing?</b>

133
00:10:44.546 --> 00:10:47.674
<b>I'll bite his head off
for a pack of cigarettes.</b>


134
00:12:00.422 --> 00:12:01.889
<b>Colonel Braddock,
I need to talk to you.</b>


135
00:12:04.759 --> 00:12:05.748
<b>Colonel.</b>

136
00:12:11.500 --> 00:12:15.163
<b>Look, I'm real sorry
those two guys died...</b>


137
00:12:15.203 --> 00:12:18.036
<b>but we don't all have to.</b>

138
00:12:18.073 --> 00:12:20.098
<b>Maybe I can get Yin
not to ride you so hard.</b>


139
00:12:20.141 --> 00:12:21.335
<b>You'd like that,
wouldn't you, Braddock?</b>


140
00:12:27.782 --> 00:12:29.113
<b>How about it, Sarge?</b>

141
00:12:29.150 --> 00:12:31.812
<b>I mean, you know you could use
some time off.</b>


142
00:12:31.853 --> 00:12:33.718
<b>Begging the captain's
pardon, sir...</b>


143
00:12:35.056 --> 00:12:39.322
<b>but kiss my black ass.</b>

144
00:12:39.361 --> 00:12:40.350
<b>That's funny.</b>

145
00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:43.288
<b>All you guys are
big, brave soldiers...</b>


146
00:12:43.331 --> 00:12:44.457
<b>and you think I'm a coward.</b>

147
00:12:44.499 --> 00:12:47.366
<b>No, you're not a coward.
You're a traitor.</b>


148
00:12:49.304 --> 00:12:50.464
<b>I'm not a traitor.</b>

149
00:12:52.207 --> 00:12:54.266
<b>Look, our country
has forgotten about us...</b>


150
00:12:54.309 --> 00:12:56.800
<b>and we have to do
anything we can to survive.</b>


151
00:12:56.845 --> 00:12:58.540
<b>Look, I'm not the bad guy here.</b>

152
00:12:58.580 --> 00:13:01.208
<b>It's Braddock
and his stupid pride.</b>


153
00:13:01.249 --> 00:13:02.443
<b>When we first got here...</b>

154
00:13:02.484 --> 00:13:05.351
<b>there were five times
as many of us... 33 Americans.</b>


155
00:13:05.387 --> 00:13:06.376
<b>Now look at us.</b>

156
00:13:07.722 --> 00:13:09.519
<b>I say that all Braddock
has to do is confess...</b>


157
00:13:09.558 --> 00:13:12.584
<b>to some garbage war crime,
and Yin will send us home.</b>


158
00:13:12.627 --> 00:13:13.753
<b>Who's gonna care?</b>

159
00:13:15.096 --> 00:13:16.791
<b>The war has been over for...</b>

160
00:13:20.001 --> 00:13:21.400
<b>for God knows how long.</b>

161
00:13:21.436 --> 00:13:22.801
<b>We don't know that for sure.</b>

162
00:13:22.837 --> 00:13:25.397
<b>There is no war.</b>

163
00:13:25.440 --> 00:13:27.738
<b>And nobody gives
a damn about us.</b>


164
00:13:27.776 --> 00:13:29.937
<b>Oh, yeah?</b>

165
00:13:29.978 --> 00:13:31.843
<b>Well, I hear they're
coming to get us.</b>


166
00:13:31.880 --> 00:13:34.405
<b>And if I were you,
I'd rather die here...</b>


167
00:13:34.449 --> 00:13:35.814
<b>than have to explain
to my kid...</b>


168
00:13:35.850 --> 00:13:37.511
<b>that I was a gutless traitor.</b>

169
00:13:39.120 --> 00:13:40.917
<b>At least I've seen my kid.</b>

170
00:13:42.524 --> 00:13:43.513
<b>Let him go.</b>

171
00:13:49.030 --> 00:13:50.463
<b>Back off, Nester.</b>

172
00:13:57.305 --> 00:13:59.239
<b>Die if you want to, all of you.</b>

173
00:14:06.815 --> 00:14:09.283
<b>Who tell you someone coming?</b>

174
00:14:09.317 --> 00:14:10.944
<b>No one.</b>

175
00:14:10.986 --> 00:14:12.817
<b>I made it up to piss him off.</b>

176
00:14:16.558 --> 00:14:18.583
<b>Why'd those guys have to run?</b>

177
00:14:18.627 --> 00:14:20.094
<b>God, I got to get some sleep!</b>

178
00:14:23.164 --> 00:14:25.689
<b>But whenever I close my eyes,
I see my wife Gina.</b>


179
00:14:30.405 --> 00:14:32.669
<b>Yeah. My Diane's
gonna be mad at me.</b>


180
00:14:34.876 --> 00:14:36.844
<b>I wanted the four kids
more than she did.</b>


181
00:14:38.647 --> 00:14:39.875
<b>We made a deal.</b>

182
00:14:42.017 --> 00:14:44.508
<b>She'd work, and I'd retire
and bring them up.</b>


183
00:14:47.989 --> 00:14:50.753
<b>I fooled the hell out of her.</b>

184
00:14:50.792 --> 00:14:52.657
<b>I haven't even seen my kid!</b>

185
00:14:59.868 --> 00:15:01.665
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

186
00:15:01.703 --> 00:15:03.637
<b>I try to block it out,
but I can't.</b>


187
00:15:03.672 --> 00:15:06.402
<b>No one can.</b>

188
00:15:06.441 --> 00:15:07.908
<b>You do. Nothing bothers you.</b>

189
00:15:09.477 --> 00:15:10.637
<b>I'm just...</b>

190
00:15:13.081 --> 00:15:14.912
<b>I'm just not tough like you.</b>

191
00:16:25.186 --> 00:16:26.175
<b>Lao.</b>

192
00:16:33.762 --> 00:16:36.560
<b>Sergeant Lawrence Opelka...</b>

193
00:16:36.598 --> 00:16:38.759
<b>you have been tried
and found guilty...</b>


194
00:16:38.800 --> 00:16:42.327
<b>of war crimes against
the people of Vietnam...</b>


195
00:16:42.370 --> 00:16:44.565
<b>and have been sentenced
to death.</b>


196
00:17:29.984 --> 00:17:31.144
<b>Please!</b>

197
00:17:37.425 --> 00:17:38.414
<b>Nester.</b>

198
00:17:41.296 --> 00:17:42.593
<b>What does he want from him?</b>

199
00:17:53.708 --> 00:17:54.970
<b>Chou, get over here!</b>

200
00:17:55.009 --> 00:17:57.068
<b>Chou! You scum!</b>

201
00:17:57.111 --> 00:17:59.102
<b>Come down here, Chou!</b>

202
00:17:59.147 --> 00:18:00.273
<b>Mazilli!</b>

203
00:18:00.315 --> 00:18:03.409
<b>Come here, Chou!
You're nothing! Chou! Chou!</b>


204
00:18:03.451 --> 00:18:06.147
<b>You lose.</b>

205
00:18:06.187 --> 00:18:07.449
<b>You're scum, Chou!</b>

206
00:18:07.488 --> 00:18:09.080
<b>Get down here
and shut that door!</b>


207
00:18:09.123 --> 00:18:10.249
<b>Mazilli!</b>

208
00:18:10.291 --> 00:18:12.452
<b>Get down here, Chou!
I said, get down here!</b>


209
00:18:12.493 --> 00:18:13.482
<b>Mazilli!</b>

210
00:18:15.797 --> 00:18:17.765
<b>It's not doing anyone any good.
You know that.</b>


211
00:18:17.799 --> 00:18:20.267
<b>What the hell is going on?</b>

212
00:18:20.301 --> 00:18:21.996
<b>Why are they starting
this torture crap again?</b>


213
00:18:33.982 --> 00:18:36.212
<b>It's OK, kid. It's OK.</b>

214
00:18:55.703 --> 00:18:57.637
<b>Here. Brought you some things.</b>

215
00:18:58.840 --> 00:19:01.138
<b>Did you get the quinine?</b>

216
00:19:01.175 --> 00:19:03.370
<b>No, I can't.
Yin has it locked up.</b>


217
00:19:03.411 --> 00:19:06.744
<b>But he told me to tell you
that if Braddock confesses...</b>


218
00:19:06.781 --> 00:19:08.009
<b>he will give it to you.</b>

219
00:19:09.617 --> 00:19:10.948
<b>Yin can't be trusted.</b>

220
00:19:13.121 --> 00:19:16.386
<b>I've given him what he wanted,
and he's treated me well enough.</b>


221
00:19:18.526 --> 00:19:20.585
