00:41:30.290 --> 00:41:32.520
<b>I hid a homing device
out there in the jungle.</b>


444
00:41:32.559 --> 00:41:34.390
<b>My team knows
exactly where I am.</b>


445
00:41:34.427 --> 00:41:36.361
<b>Now, they'll be waiting
for my signal.</b>


446
00:41:36.396 --> 00:41:37.863
<b>Now, if I give it,
they'll come in slowly.</b>


447
00:41:37.897 --> 00:41:39.990
<b>If I don't, they'll come in
fast, and you'll all be dead.</b>


448
00:41:40.033 --> 00:41:41.500
<b>What signal?</b>

449
00:41:41.534 --> 00:41:42.899
<b>Stop playing the fool.</b>

450
00:41:44.704 --> 00:41:45.932
<b>The way I figure it...</b>

451
00:41:45.972 --> 00:41:49.669
<b>these are your choices...
you can either cut and run...</b>


452
00:41:49.709 --> 00:41:51.301
<b>or you can wait
until my team comes in...</b>


453
00:41:51.344 --> 00:41:53.869
<b>and then you can try to run...</b>

454
00:41:53.913 --> 00:41:56.074
<b>or you can cooperate
right now...</b>


455
00:41:56.116 --> 00:41:58.175
<b>and save everyone
a whole lot of trouble.</b>


456
00:42:03.957 --> 00:42:07.154
<b>I believe you left out
some of my options.</b>


457
00:42:07.193 --> 00:42:11.425
<b>One, I could kill you
and the prisoners.</b>


458
00:42:12.699 --> 00:42:14.223
<b>Yes. Missed that one.</b>

459
00:42:14.267 --> 00:42:18.431
<b>And two... I can simply
lock you up...</b>


460
00:42:18.471 --> 00:42:22.567
<b>and wait until you're ready
to give the signal.</b>


461
00:42:22.609 --> 00:42:24.133
<b>Yes, you could lock me up...</b>

462
00:42:24.177 --> 00:42:25.906
<b>but I'll never give you
the signal.</b>


463
00:42:25.945 --> 00:42:27.173
<b>I don't care if you kill me.</b>

464
00:42:27.213 --> 00:42:30.376
<b>Now, look, I'm tired of
hanging around under this sun...</b>


465
00:42:30.417 --> 00:42:32.942
<b>playing footsie with
a half-pint would-be dictator.</b>


466
00:42:52.806 --> 00:42:55.297
<b>Give him anything he wants.</b>

467
00:42:55.342 --> 00:42:56.468
<b>I can't believe it!</b>

468
00:42:56.509 --> 00:42:59.307
<b>We're going home!</b>

469
00:42:59.346 --> 00:43:02.804
<b>OK. I want to know who won
the World Series last year.</b>


470
00:43:02.849 --> 00:43:05.613
<b>I don't know anything about
any bloody World Series, mate.</b>


471
00:43:05.652 --> 00:43:06.778
<b>I'm Australian.</b>

472
00:43:06.820 --> 00:43:08.151
<b>Forget it. I love you anyway.</b>

473
00:43:12.425 --> 00:43:14.086
<b>Yin won't give up this easy.</b>

474
00:43:14.127 --> 00:43:15.992
<b>How large is your rescue team?</b>

475
00:43:16.029 --> 00:43:17.519
<b>Large enough to kick
Yin's ass, huh?</b>


476
00:43:21.034 --> 00:43:22.023
<b>I'm alone.</b>

477
00:43:26.506 --> 00:43:27.837
<b>Alone?</b>

478
00:43:27.874 --> 00:43:29.569
<b>Nobody knows I'm here, mate.</b>

479
00:43:31.277 --> 00:43:33.472
<b>Man, there's nobody
gonna come and get me.</b>


480
00:43:33.513 --> 00:43:35.743
<b>But the International
Freedom House...</b>


481
00:43:35.782 --> 00:43:37.613
<b>The Central Team,
The homing device?</b>


482
00:43:37.650 --> 00:43:39.777
<b>It's just a bluff, isn't it?
I had to tell him something.</b>


483
00:43:39.819 --> 00:43:41.377
<b>I've heard rumors
about this place.</b>


484
00:43:41.421 --> 00:43:42.683
<b>I followed Francois in.</b>

485
00:43:42.722 --> 00:43:44.280
<b>I'm just a lousy
photographer, mate.</b>


486
00:43:44.324 --> 00:43:46.622
<b>I needed pictures for proof.</b>

487
00:43:46.659 --> 00:43:47.785
<b>Damn!</b>

488
00:43:47.827 --> 00:43:51.319
<b>One thing for sure,
he's got guts.</b>


489
00:43:51.364 --> 00:43:56.734
<b>Yeah. Nobody ever broke
into a prison camp.</b>


490
00:43:56.770 --> 00:43:59.603
<b>All right, then, let's get out.
We'll head for the cliffs.</b>


491
00:43:59.639 --> 00:44:00.765
<b>Anything happens to me...</b>

492
00:44:00.807 --> 00:44:02.035
<b>I stashed
some ropes under a big rock.</b>


493
00:44:02.075 --> 00:44:03.337
<b>You can't miss it.
Head for the Thai border...</b>


494
00:44:03.376 --> 00:44:04.741
<b>100 miles due west.
Come on, let's go.</b>


495
00:44:04.778 --> 00:44:08.111
<b>Wait. Yin may let you go...</b>

496
00:44:08.148 --> 00:44:10.412
<b>but he certainly
won't let us all go.</b>


497
00:44:10.450 --> 00:44:11.678
<b>What's that?</b>

498
00:44:11.718 --> 00:44:14.812
<b>It's Francois coming
to pick up his whores.</b>


499
00:44:14.854 --> 00:44:16.719
<b>Shit. He knows I'm alone.</b>

500
00:44:16.756 --> 00:44:17.745
<b>Well, move it!</b>

501
00:44:21.928 --> 00:44:24.089
<b>I'm just going to give
the signal, mate.</b>


502
00:44:34.808 --> 00:44:36.275
<b>Mr. Emerson.</b>

503
00:44:36.309 --> 00:44:37.537
<b>I'm just gonna give my signal.</b>

504
00:44:37.577 --> 00:44:38.703
<b>Good.</b>

505
00:44:38.745 --> 00:44:40.212
<b>Damn.</b>

506
00:44:40.246 --> 00:44:42.908
<b>I hope everyone's told you
how well they have been treated.</b>


507
00:44:42.949 --> 00:44:44.280
<b>Well, they don't love you,
but all in all...</b>


508
00:44:44.317 --> 00:44:45.784
<b>they look pretty good.
I'll be right back.</b>


509
00:44:45.819 --> 00:44:47.309
<b>One more moment, please.</b>

510
00:44:49.923 --> 00:44:52.118
<b>I would like you to meet
a friend of mine.</b>


511
00:44:52.158 --> 00:44:54.092
<b>I'll meet him later.
I'm in a bit of a hurry.</b>


512
00:44:54.127 --> 00:44:56.459
<b>I wouldn't want the Central Team
to get impatient, you know.</b>


513
00:44:56.496 --> 00:44:57.690
<b>Francois.</b>

514
00:44:59.199 --> 00:45:02.760
<b>What's the matter, my friend?
You look a little nervous.</b>


515
00:45:02.802 --> 00:45:05.965
<b>He is the goddamn guy who's
been asking questions about us.</b>


516
00:45:06.005 --> 00:45:10.237
<b>He claims he's the point man
for a major rescue operation.</b>


517
00:45:10.276 --> 00:45:13.575
<b>He's lying. 
He's alone.</b>

518
00:45:13.613 --> 00:45:15.581
<b>I've still got the homing
device out in the jungle.</b>


519
00:45:22.722 --> 00:45:25.350
<b>I am weary of playing footsie
with you.</b>


520
00:45:27.927 --> 00:45:29.155
<b>Take him to the tree.</b>

521
00:45:32.432 --> 00:45:33.626
<b>Move!</b>

522
00:45:51.518 --> 00:45:55.511
<b>For the crimes against
the people of Vietnam...</b>


523
00:45:55.555 --> 00:45:57.455
<b>I sentence you to death.</b>

524
00:46:02.462 --> 00:46:04.692
<b>Don't worry! 
It's not real!</b>

525
00:46:04.731 --> 00:46:06.358
<b>He's just trying to scare you!</b>

526
00:46:06.399 --> 00:46:08.458
<b>They've got
a lousy sense of humor.</b>


527
00:46:23.917 --> 00:46:26.818
<b>Get up. Get up.</b>

528
00:46:28.221 --> 00:46:29.882
<b>Shut up, you asshole.</b>

529
00:46:29.923 --> 00:46:31.151
<b>You...</b>

530
00:46:31.190 --> 00:46:32.782
<b>We'll get him up.</b>

531
00:46:32.825 --> 00:46:33.883
<b>OK, OK.</b>

532
00:46:36.195 --> 00:46:37.924
<b>I'm OK.</b>

533
00:46:48.441 --> 00:46:49.430
<b>Captain Ho?</b>

534
00:47:07.627 --> 00:47:08.855
<b>He's dying.</b>

535
00:47:24.644 --> 00:47:25.633
<b>Yin!</b>

536
00:47:43.296 --> 00:47:44.854
<b>No, don't do it.</b>

537
00:47:44.897 --> 00:47:46.057
<b>He has to.</b>

538
00:47:48.735 --> 00:47:49.929
<b>What the hell's the difference?</b>

539
00:47:54.340 --> 00:47:57.138
<b>Our struggle was a long one.</b>

540
00:47:57.176 --> 00:48:00.475
<b>As I predicted, you lost.</b>

541
00:48:00.513 --> 00:48:07.077
<b>I'm glad you finally understand
the extent of your guilt.</b>


542
00:48:07.120 --> 00:48:08.417
<b>You do, don't you?</b>

543
00:48:08.454 --> 00:48:10.786
<b>He don't understand shit!</b>

544
00:48:15.461 --> 00:48:16.689
<b>Yes, Colonel Yin...</b>

545
00:48:18.498 --> 00:48:20.159
<b>I understand.</b>

546
00:48:34.914 --> 00:48:36.245
<b>Let's get him up.</b>

547
00:48:41.788 --> 00:48:43.016
<b>Colonel Braddock.</b>

548
00:48:45.825 --> 00:48:48.020
<b>I believe you have
forgotten something.</b>


549
00:49:05.712 --> 00:49:08.112
<b>Now, my American P.O. W...</b>

550
00:49:08.147 --> 00:49:11.844
<b>I will live up to my promise
and will let you go free.</b>


551
00:49:11.884 --> 00:49:15.945
<b>Tomorrow, Francois will be here
and will fly you to Thailand...</b>


552
00:49:15.988 --> 00:49:18.456
<b>and deliver you to your embassy.</b>

553
00:49:18.491 --> 00:49:20.516
<b>You see, Colonel? 
I told you.</b>

554
00:49:22.528 --> 00:49:24.655
<b>I will try to make
your last day here...</b>


555
00:49:24.697 --> 00:49:26.187
<b>as comfortable as possible.</b>

556
00:49:26.232 --> 00:49:30.498
<b>Here. Come into the next room.
You'll stay there tonight.</b>


557
00:49:54.594 --> 00:49:56.562
<b>I can't believe it.</b>

558
00:49:56.596 --> 00:49:58.325
<b>It's over. We're going home.</b>

559
00:49:58.364 --> 00:50:00.025
<b>I'm going to see my kid!</b>

560
00:50:01.434 --> 00:50:02.833
<b>Something's wrong.</b>

561
00:50:02.869 --> 00:50:04.063
<b>Nothing's wrong.</b>

562
00:50:04.103 --> 00:50:05.400
<b>You've just been here too long.</b>

563
00:50:05.438 --> 00:50:06.769
<b>You're in shock.</b>

564
00:50:06.806 --> 00:50:08.137
<b>I am feeling better.</b>

565
00:50:08.174 --> 00:50:09.334
<b>Yeah, you're feeling better.</b>

566
00:50:16.682 --> 00:50:18.547
<b>Nothing works this fast.</b>

567
00:50:21.087 --> 00:50:23.078
<b>Oh, God! Get him up, Mazilli!</b>

568
00:50:23.122 --> 00:50:24.680
<b>He's been poisoned!</b>

569
00:50:24.724 --> 00:50:26.885
<b>Come on, Franklin!</b>

570
00:50:26.926 --> 00:50:28.052
<b>Come on, on both legs.</b>

571
00:50:28.094 --> 00:50:29.220
<b>Walk!</b>

572
00:50:29.262 --> 00:50:30.957
<b>- Come on.
- Walk, Franklin.</b>


573
00:50:30.997 --> 00:50:33.431
<b>Come on, walk it.
Walk, Franklin!</b>


574
00:50:33.466 --> 00:50:35.593
<b>Is this an American
funeral rite?</b>


575
00:50:37.069 --> 00:50:43.941
<b>I'm afraid I gave poor Franklin
such an overdose of opium...</b>


576
00:50:43.976 --> 00:50:47.605
<b>that he could walk
from here to Los Angeles...</b>


577
00:50:47.647 --> 00:50:49.706
<b>and would not do him any good.</b>

578
00:50:53.486 --> 00:50:54.612
<b>Throw him in the hole.</b>

579
00:50:54.654 --> 00:50:56.645
<b>You son of a bitch.</b>

580
00:51:43.403 --> 00:51:44.700
<b>Wait!</b>

581
00:51:46.306 --> 00:51:49.833
<b>Yin, wait!</b>

582
00:51:49.877 --> 00:51:51.344
<b>Yin!</b>

583
00:51:55.249 --> 00:51:56.739
<b>He's not dead!</b>

584
00:52:00.554 --> 00:52:02.044
<b>God, no!</b>

585
00:52:02.089 --> 00:52:03.681
<b>Oh, God!</b>

586
00:52:10.464 --> 00:52:11.692
<b>Son of a bitch.</b>

587
00:59:01.341 --> 00:59:05.607
<b>Mazilli, I thought
you should know...</b>


588
00:59:05.645 --> 00:59:07.636
<b>that you're completely alone.</b>

589
00:59:07.681 --> 00:59:12.482
<b>Your brave colonel has abandoned
you to die here.</b>


590
00:59:12.519 --> 00:59:13.747
<b>Braddock got away?</b>

591
00:59:13.787 --> 00:59:15.254
<b>He'll die tomorrow.</b>

592
00:59:16.656 --> 00:59:17.816
<b>So will you.</b>

593
00:59:19.192 --> 00:59:20.523
<b>In the meantime...</b>

594
00:59:23.863 --> 00:59:25.694
<b>if you're lonely...</b>

595
00:59:28.935 --> 00:59:30.732
<b>play with your friend.</b>

596
00:59:54.527 --> 00:59:55.892
<b>More wine, Colonel?</b>

597
00:59:55.929 --> 00:59:56.918
<b>No.</b>

598
01:00:00.567 --> 01:00:02.296
<b>Braddock gone!</b>

599
01:00:02.335 --> 01:00:03.734
<b>Why keep him alive?</b>

600
01:00:05.639 --> 01:00:07.038
<b>Now, you know,
I might be wrong...</b>


601
01:00:07.073 --> 01:00:10.804
<b>but I don't think it's
a very good idea to kill me.</b>


602
01:00:10.844 --> 01:00:13.176
<b>Why not?</b>

603
01:00:13.213 --> 01:00:16.273
<b>I could always get
someone to pour my wine.</b>


604
01:00:19.452 --> 01:00:22.012
<b>It's because
I'm the only one left...</b>


605
01:00:22.055 --> 01:00:25.286
<b>who really knows how
Colonel Braddock thinks.</b>


606
01:00:25.325 --> 01:00:26.758
<b>See, he hasn't gone yet.</b>

607
01:00:29.296 --> 01:00:30.786
<b>Is that so?</b>

608
01:00:30.830 --> 01:00:34.698
<b>Yes. He has stayed to try
and take revenge on you.</b>


609
01:00:42.208 --> 01:00:44.733
<b>I will use Francois' helicopter.</b>

610
01:00:44.778 --> 01:00:46.473
<b>We will capture him tomorrow.</b>

611
01:00:50.583 --> 01:00:53.245
<b>We should have killed that guy
a long time ago.</b>


612
01:03:18.832 --> 01:03:20.527
<b>We'd better get back.</b>

613
01:03:20.567 --> 01:03:22.296
<b>You'll never find
this guy alive.</b>


614
01:03:22.335 --> 01:03:23.495
<b>Just keep searching.</b>

615
01:04:46.085 --> 01:04:47.985
<b>Braddock come back,
blow bridge down.</b>


616
01:04:48.021 --> 01:04:50.285
<b>Lock up all the prisoners
and Nester!</b>


617
01:04:50.323 --> 01:04:51.483
<b>You, to the bridge!</b>

618
01:04:55.261 --> 01:04:56.421
<b>In there.</b>

619
01:05:04.637 --> 01:05:06.605
<b>I'll bury him with this.</b>

620
01:05:09.542 --> 01:05:11.772
<b>My God! It's a bomb!</b>

621
01:05:11.811 --> 01:05:12.800
<b>Get out!</b>

622
01:05:21.888 --> 01:05:23.287
<b>Damn American!</b>

623
01:05:57.390 --> 01:05:58.516
<b>Open it.</b>

624
01:05:58.558 --> 01:05:59.547
<b>Mazilli!</b>

625
01:06:02.161 --> 01:06:03.492
<b>What the hell?</b>

626
01:06:03.529 --> 01:06:05.326
<b>Braddock!</b>

627
01:06:05.365 --> 01:06:06.389
<b>Let's go!</b>

628
01:06:08.835 --> 01:06:09.767
<b>Duck!</b>

629
01:06:15.074 --> 01:06:16.507
<b>Come on! Come on!</b>

630
01:07:04.857 --> 01:07:07.849
<b>Damn! We got to find that rope.</b>

631
01:07:13.633 --> 01:07:15.999
<b>They're getting too close.
Let's get out of here.</b>


632
01:07:16.035 --> 01:07:17.332
<b>It's got to be here.</b>

633
01:07:20.173 --> 01:07:21.663
<b>Emerson said
they were under a big rock.</b>


634
01:07:21.708 --> 01:07:23.073
<b>There must be 60 big rocks.</b>

635
01:07:27.880 --> 01:07:28.869
<b>Here it is!</b>

636
01:07:30.950 --> 01:07:31.939
<b>Here.</b>

637
01:07:46.499 --> 01:07:47.761
<b>Good luck, kid.</b>

638
01:07:47.800 --> 01:07:50.268
<b>- Aren't you coming?
- I'm going after Ho.</b>


639
01:07:50.303 --> 01:07:53.500
<b>If you're staying to fight,
there's no way I'm leaving you.</b>


640
01:07:53.539 --> 01:07:55.973
<b>Here they come!
Get your ass down the cliff!</b>


641
01:12:06.058 --> 01:12:07.389
<b>You idiot!</b>

642
01:12:14.600 --> 01:12:15.760
<b>Come in.</b>

643
01:12:17.470 --> 01:12:20.496
<b>So, Yin, we're all loaded up.</b>

644
01:12:20.539 --> 01:12:23.099
<b>I'll see you in about a week.</b>

645
01:12:23.142 --> 01:12:26.805
<b>Francois, I will need
your helicopter...</b>


646
01:12:26.846 --> 01:12:28.245
<b>to look for the Americans.</b>

647
01:12:28.280 --> 01:12:30.145
<b>I believe they've gone down
the river.</b>


648
01:12:30.182 --> 01:12:31.911
<b>I am sorry. 
I can't help you.</b>

649
01:12:31.951 --> 01:12:33.282
<b>You will not go.</b>

650
01:12:34.887 --> 01:12:37.185
<b>I am going.</b>

651
01:12:37.223 --> 01:12:38.656
<b>Come on, let's go.</b>

652
01:12:38.691 --> 01:12:42.127
<b>Get your hands off...
What the hell are you doing?</b>


653
01:12:42.161 --> 01:12:44.425
<b>They are following my order.</b>

654
01:12:45.765 --> 01:12:50.759
<b>They needed a new leader after
they heard that you had died.</b>


655
01:14:16.956 --> 01:14:17.945
<b>Ho.</b>

656
01:16:07.032 --> 01:16:08.226
<b>Opelka.</b>

657
01:16:08.267 --> 01:16:09.427
<b>Colonel.</b>

658
01:16:18.077 --> 01:16:19.442
<b>I'm glad you made it, kid.</b>

659
01:16:19.478 --> 01:16:22.777
<b>Thanks, Colonel.
Yin must have given up on me.</b>


660
01:16:22.815 --> 01:16:24.077
<b>He thought you were dead.</b>

661
01:16:25.818 --> 01:16:27.479
<b>How come you hung around?</b>

662
01:16:27.519 --> 01:16:28.679
<b>I don't know.</b>

663
01:16:30.155 --> 01:16:32.020
<b>I guess it was just
some kind of instinct.</b>


664
01:16:37.963 --> 01:16:40.363
<b>I want you to guard the base.</b>

665
01:16:40.399 --> 01:16:42.128
<b>If I'm not back in 24 hours...</b>

666
01:16:42.167 --> 01:16:43.896
<b>go down the river
and try to find Mazilli.</b>


667
01:16:46.171 --> 01:16:51.438
<b>Colonel, I know you don't need
me to guard the base.</b>


668
01:16:51.477 --> 01:16:53.707
<b>I want to help you
get those bastards.</b>


669
01:17:03.422 --> 01:17:04.582
<b>Colonel Braddock!</b>

670
01:17:17.002 --> 01:17:18.936
<b>Yin's our enemy, too.</b>

671
01:17:21.440 --> 01:17:22.600
<b>I'll kill him!</b>

672
01:17:24.009 --> 01:17:27.536
<b>The fighting's over!
We all go home!</b>


673
01:17:29.248 --> 01:17:30.374
<b>Colonel Braddock!</b>

674
01:17:30.416 --> 01:17:31.405
<b>Dou Chou.</b>

675
01:17:34.019 --> 01:17:35.680
<b>He's listening.
He knows we're here.</b>


676
01:17:44.697 --> 01:17:47.257
<b>Yin dead. Believe now.</b>

677
01:17:47.299 --> 01:17:49.199
<b>See, Colonel Braddock?</b>

678
01:17:50.769 --> 01:17:52.703
<b>Come look for yourself.
Yin dead!</b>


679
01:17:56.141 --> 01:17:58.575
<b>Sir, the boots. 
That's not Yin.</b>

680
01:18:13.926 --> 01:18:15.052
<b>I'm going after Ho.</b>

681
01:18:15.094 --> 01:18:16.789
<b>He's in one of those two shacks
down there.</b>


682
01:18:16.829 --> 01:18:20.788
<b>If there's any fireworks,
here, throw these grenades.</b>


683
01:18:22.234 --> 01:18:24.828
<b>Sir, what about Nester?</b>

684
01:18:24.870 --> 01:18:26.804
<b>He can take care of himself.</b>

685
01:18:26.839 --> 01:18:27.999
<b>He always has.</b>

686
01:18:32.077 --> 01:18:33.237
<b>He won't show.</b>

687
01:18:39.318 --> 01:18:40.478
<b>He'll come.</b>

688
01:19:00.539 --> 01:19:02.507
<b>Good. They got Mazilli.</b>

689
01:19:02.541 --> 01:19:03.530
<b>Let's go.</b>

690
01:19:21.026 --> 01:19:23.085
<b>Colonel Braddock!</b>

691
01:19:33.272 --> 01:19:36.901
<b>I'll give you

692
01:19:36.942 --> 01:19:40.139
<b>whether you want Mazilli
to live or die.</b>


693
01:20:02.167 --> 01:20:04.362
<b>Your 30 seconds is up!</b>

694
01:20:05.737 --> 01:20:10.037
<b>You have just murdered
your last man.</b>


695
01:20:10.075 --> 01:20:12.543
<b>Psst. Mazilli...</b>

696
01:20:12.578 --> 01:20:14.808
<b>anything you want me
to tell your kid?</b>


697
01:20:17.683 --> 01:20:19.480
<b>Hold it!</b>

698
01:20:19.518 --> 01:20:20.815
<b>Mazilli is mine.</b>

699
01:20:22.788 --> 01:20:24.813
<b>Why don't we just tell
the kid that Daddy...</b>


700
01:20:24.857 --> 01:20:30.193
<b>was a very brave soldier
right up till the very end?</b>


701
01:20:35.234 --> 01:20:36.292
<b>Down!</b>

702
01:20:39.905 --> 01:20:41.202
<b>Move it, Mazilli!</b>

703
01:21:06.365 --> 01:21:08.697
<b>Nester... he came back to us.</b>

704
01:21:08.734 --> 01:21:09.723
<b>Yeah, I know.</b>

705
01:21:11.069 --> 01:21:12.229
<b>I'm going after Ho.</b>

706
01:21:34.092 --> 01:21:35.923
<b>Cover us, Ho. 
We're going in.</b>

707
01:21:45.103 --> 01:21:48.072
<b>Colonel, they're all
in Yin's house.</b>


708
01:21:48.106 --> 01:21:49.334
<b>Opelka!</b>

709
01:21:49.374 --> 01:21:50.363
<b>Lieutenant.</b>

710
01:21:55.247 --> 01:21:56.737
<b>Opelka, left flank.</b>

711
01:21:58.283 --> 01:22:00.911
<b>Mazilli, around back.</b>

712
01:22:00.953 --> 01:22:02.079
<b>Wait.</b>

713
01:22:02.120 --> 01:22:04.020
<b>Ready? Go!</b>

714
01:22:04.056 --> 01:22:05.353
<b>Now!</b>

715
01:23:43.221 --> 01:23:44.654
<b>Nobody could have lived
through this.</b>


716
01:23:46.591 --> 01:23:47.580
<b>Colonel.</b>

717
01:24:11.383 --> 01:24:12.873
<b>Remember how to fly this thing?</b>

718
01:24:12.918 --> 01:24:14.078
<b>You better believe it.</b>

719
01:25:17.716 --> 01:25:19.775
<b>You really didn't think
I'd leave...</b>


720
01:25:19.818 --> 01:25:21.479
<b>without knowing for sure
you were dead?</b>


721
01:25:24.556 --> 01:25:26.786
<b>You'll not just kill me.</b>

722
01:25:26.825 --> 01:25:29.988
<b>You want to know
who the better man is.</b>


723
01:25:31.329 --> 01:25:35.629
<b>That is why you stayed behind.</b>

724
01:25:35.667 --> 01:25:38.227
<b>I also want to know.</b>

725
01:25:38.270 --> 01:25:42.707
<b>That is why I kept you alive
all these years.</b>


726
01:25:46.011 --> 01:25:48.536
<b>Now it is the time...</b>

727
01:25:48.580 --> 01:25:52.710
<b>You and I, one-on-one.</b>

728
01:25:52.751 --> 01:25:53.911
<b>No politics...</b>

729
01:25:55.420 --> 01:25:56.910
<b>no weapons.</b>

730
01:26:05.730 --> 01:26:10.258
<b>Just a little game to find out
who is the better man.</b>


731
01:26:15.607 --> 01:26:18.576
<b>I knew you could not
resist my challenge.</b>


732
01:26:27.085 --> 01:26:30.521
<b>Colonel Yin,
for the atrocities inflicted...</b>


733
01:26:30.555 --> 01:26:33.285
<b>on the Vietnamese and American
prisoners of this camp...</b>


734
01:26:35.160 --> 01:26:37.128
<b>I sentence you to death.</b>

735
01:28:41.553 --> 01:28:42.952
<b>This is for Nester.</b>

736
01:28:52.330 --> 01:28:53.558
<b>Not yet.</b>

737
01:29:24.896 --> 01:29:26.761
<b>The game's over.</b>

738
01:30:03.468 --> 01:30:05.197
<b>And this is for Franklin.</b>

739
01:30:14.712 --> 01:30:16.043
<b>You lose.</b>

740
01:31:13.104 --> 01:31:14.264
<b>This is for me.</b>